    "asOf": "2021-04-29",
    "date": "2022-02-08T14:52:43Z",
    "text": "Administrative Pay-As-You-Go Act of 2021\n\nThis bill provides statutory authority for the Office of Management and Budget (OMB) requirement that federal agencies must submit at least one proposal for reducing direct spending before taking a discretionary administrative action that increases direct spending. Further, an agency must submit to the OMB its legal basis for concluding that a proposed administrative action is nondiscretionary and, therefore, not subject to this requirement."
